al Kombat II]]''\n| [[Acclaim Entertainment]]\n| [[Fighting game|Fighting]]\n| 4\n| #1\n|}\n\n===Highest-renting console titles according to Blockbuster Video===\n[[Blockbuster LLC|Blockbuster Video]], an American chain of [[video rental shop]]s, released a ''[[GamePro]]''-exclusive monthly list of the chain's highest-renting console titles.<ref name=\"GameProFeb1994\">{{cite magazine |url=https://retrocdn.net/images/1/11/GamePro_US_055.pdf |title=Blockbuster Video Top 10 Video Game Rentals |magazine=[[GamePro]] |date=February 1994 |pages=188}}</ref><ref name=\"GameProMar1994\">{{cite magazine |url=https://retrocdn.net/images/5/56/GamePro_US_056.pdf |title=Blockbuster Video Top 10 Video Game Rentals |magazine=[[GamePro]] |date=March 1994 |pages=188}}</ref><ref name=\"GameProApr1994\">{{cite magazine |url=https://retrocdn.net/images/2/28/GamePro_US_057.pdf |title=Blockbuster Video Top 10 Video Game Rentals |magazine=[[GamePro]] |date=April 1994 |pages=178}}</ref><ref name=\"GameProMay1994\">{{cite magazine |url=https://retrocdn.net/images/e/ed/GamePro_US_058.pdf |title=Blockbuster Video Top 10 Video Game Rentals |magazine=[[GamePro]] |date=May 1994 |pages=170}}</ref><ref name=\"GameProJun1994\">{{cite magazine |url=https://retrocdn.net/images/b/bf/GamePro_US_059.pdf |title=Blockbuster Video Top 10 Video Game Rentals |magazine=[[GamePro]] |date=June 1994 |pages=188}}</ref><ref name=\"GameProJul1994\">{{cite magazine |url=https://retrocdn.net/images/9/92/GamePro_US_060.pdf |title=Blockbuster Video Top 10 Video Game Rentals |magazine=[[GamePro]] |date=July 1994 |pages=188}}</ref><ref name=\"GameProAug1994\">{{cite magazine |url=https://retrocdn.net/images/f/f1/GamePro_US_061.pdf |title=Blockbuster Video August Hot Sheet! |magazine=[[GamePro]] |date=August 1994 |pages=188}}</ref><ref name=\"GameProSep1994\">{{cite magazine |url=https://retrocdn.net/images/e/e0/GamePro_US_062.pdf |title=Blockbuster Video September Hot Sheet! |magazine=[[GamePro]] |date=September 1994 |pages=162}}</ref><ref name=\"GameProOct1994\">{{cite magazine |url=https://retrocdn.net/images/6/61/GamePro_US_063.pdf |title=Blockbuster Video October Hot Sheet! |magazine=[[GamePro]] |date=October 1994 |pages=179}}</ref><ref name=\"GameProNov1994\">{{cite magazine |url=https://retrocdn.net/images/9/9f/GamePro_US_064.pdf |title=Blockbuster Video November Hot Sheet! |magazine=[[GamePro]] |date=November 1994 |pages=275}}</ref><ref name=\"GameProDec1994\">{{cite magazine |url=https://retrocdn.net/images/b/b1/GamePro_US_065.pdf |title=Blockbuster Video December Hot Sheet! |magazine=[[GamePro]] |date=December 1994 |pages=275}}</ref><ref name=\"GameProJan1995\">{{cite magazine |url=https://retrocdn.net/images/5/5d/GamePro_US_066.pdf |title=Blockbuster Video January Hot Sheet! |magazine=[[GamePro]] |date=January 1995 |pages=212}}</ref>\n\n;Highest-renting [[Nintendo Entertainment System|NES]] titles of 1994\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! Title !! Publisher !! Genre(s) !! # of charting months !! Peak position\n|-\n| ''[[Kirby's Adventure]]''\n| [[Nintendo]]\n| [[Platform game|Platform]]\n| 12\n| #1\n|-\n| ''[[Tetris 2 (1993 video game)|Tetris 2]]''\n| [[Nintendo]]\n| [[Puzzle video game|Puzzle]]\n| 12\n| #2\n|-\n| ''[[The Ren & Stimpy Show#Video games|The Ren & Stimpy Show: Buckeroo$]]''\n| [[THQ]]\n| [[Action game|Action]]\n| 11\n| #3\n|-\n| ''[[Mega Man 6]]''\n| [[Capcom]]\n| [[Platform game|Platform]]\n| 9\n| #1\n|-\n| ''[[Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles: Tournament Fighters]]''\n| [[Konami]]\n| [[Fighting game|Fighting]]\n| 9\n| #2\n|-\n| ''[[Jurassic Park (NES video game)|Jurassic Park]]''\n| [[Ocean Software]]\n| [[Action-adventure game|Action-adventure]]\n| 8\n| #4\n|-\n| ''[[Mario is Missing!]]''\n| [[The Software Toolworks]]\n| [[Educational game|Educational]]\n| 8\n| #5\n|-\n| ''[[WWF King of the Ring]]''\n| [[Acclaim Entertainment]]\n| [[Fighting game|Fighting]]\n| 8\n| #7\n|-\n| ''[[Tecmo Super Bowl]]''\n| [[Tecmo]]\n| [[Sports game|